<br>
As a (STILL) lvl 54 cleric, I got tired of spending 80pp a night hoping around trying to find a group to exp with.<br>
<br>
I got SOOO tired of it, I created a second account and leveled a warrior to group with my cleric.  god knows.. I couldn't solo without sitting for 30 minutes between kills.<br>
<br>
THE single biggest issue with improving heals for druids and shaman are the &quot;exp grind&quot; groups.<br>
<br>
who the hell needs a cleric when you have a shaman slowing, ACH and torpor?<br>
<br>
Who the hell needs a cleric when you a a druid casting regen, ACH and evac?<br>
<br>
Who the hell needs a cleric when you can '/shout WTB REZ' and receive 5 responses?<br>
<br>
In the meantime, the clerics continue to go /LFG ON, or log to play an alt.<br>
<br>
Please, don't respond with RAID issues, NO ONE disputes the need for clerics on raids, thus the arguement is invalid.  Lets keep this on the normal experience grind groups, where the clerics have basically, buff/heal jobs only.. where now others would bring MORE to the table.<br>
<br>
So.. hell yes, give me more SOLO capability.. so when I cant find a group, I can still get to lvl 56 to give your ass a 96% rez..<br>
<br>
Think about it..  It's all fun and games, until the clerics cant rez you anymore. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=198804>Impudent Blasphemy</a><BR>
