<br>
I see. You make such a strong compelling case.<br>
<br>
Letting Clerics solo some and Druids heal more does not break the game in any way. Many people don't play clerics because they are too one dimensional and too dependent. Anything to ease that is a good thing. Letting druids get better heals so that possibly several can sub for one cleric is also a good thing. Clerics are too far and few between and that very fact exacerbates cleric burnout. Yes they enjoy a privileged position, but they also feel a lot of pressure to participate in raids. Maybe it would be nice to just relax solo or duo some evenings and leisurely get some xp without the very intense pressure of even just a grind group much less a raid.<br>
<br>
Clerics will never solo like druids nor Druids heal like clerics.<br>
<br>
I find it odd so many (not all) want the enhancement for their own class but don't want the complementary enhancement for the other.<br>
<br>
This isn't mass. This isn't the military. Tradition has little place in EQ. It's less than 5 years old and it will evolve as long as it exists.<br>
<br>
