<br>
It would be a big mistake for anyone to think that this heal will replace clerics. Your heals are faster, more mana efficient, you can rezz, and if you have the mana to spare because the mobs I have slowed aren't doing much damage, you have some decent nukes.<br>
<br>
EDIT: currently it takes roughly 2 secondary healers to begin to compensate for a cleric. Because there is a 75% cap on the heal, 2 of us won't be as efficient as there is a 75% cap, which has been show to realistically be only 60-65% as we don't generally heal when someone is at 1 hp.  The best use of this will be on raids or in groups that are unable to get a cleric. I think the reason clerics have tough times getting to groups is because groups need just one, and if those groups have already filled the spot with a druid or a shaman in a pinch (no cleric to be found), that really can't be helped. Not fair to kick out the healer because a cleric shows up is it? <p><table border=0>
